elements.title: St. Mary and St. John of Nepomuk Monument
elements.contents: ... that the St. Mary and St. John of Nepomuk Monument in Timișoara commemorates the Great Plague of 1738, which killed around 1,000 of the city's 6,000 inhabitants?

elements.title: Bastable Theatre
elements.contents: ... that after Syracuse's Bastable Theatre burnt down in 1923, the city's tallest building was built in its place?

elements.title: a 2007 European Court of Human Rights case
elements.contents: ... that a 2007 European Court of Human Rights case ruled that European automobile owners do not have the right to remain silent when asked who was speeding in their vehicle?

elements.title: Operation Ivory Soap
elements.contents: ... that Operation Ivory Soap created and operated a fleet of aircraft repair vessels to support the United States' island-hopping strategy in the Pacific during World War II?

elements.title: Charles William Warner
elements.contents: ... that Charles William Warner, the attorney general of Trinidad between 1845 and 1870, was one of the most powerful men in the colony and often considered "the real governor"?

elements.title: operetta composed by John Philip Sousa
elements.contents: ... that El Capitan, an operetta composed by John Philip Sousa, was later described as likely to become "the most enduring American comic opera of the nineteenth century"?

elements.title: Cheok Hong Cheong
